OL,6,FErith Plant Services Limited, of Queen
OL,7,FStreet, Erith, Kent pleaded guilty to
OL,8,Fbreaching Section 2(1) of the Health
OL,9,Fand Safety at Work etc. Act 1974.
OL,11,FThe company was fined #175,000 and
OL,12,Fordered to pay #37,804 in costs.
OL,14,FHSE inspector Joanne Williams said:
OL,15,F"This tragic death serves as an
OL,16,Fimportant reminder that workers need
OL,17,Fto be trained and that there is always
OL,18,Fthe potential for an attachment to
OL,19,Ffall during the operation of
OL,20,Fexcavators.
